<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-11T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20/254a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-11T14:00:00-04:00">November
                                    11, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>574. Effective on the date when the <hi rend="italic">Gendarmerie</hi>
                            contract is signed, the War Department, with the concurrence of the
                            Department of State, is relieving Colonel Schwarzkopf from assignment to
                            duty with the American Minister at Tehran and assigning him as Chief of
                            the United States Army Mission to Iran in connection with the
                            reorganization of the Iranian <hi rend="italic">Gendarmerie</hi>.</p>
                        <p>Schwarzkopf will discuss this with you on his return.<note n="68" xml:id="d586fn68">Colonel Schwarzkopf had been in the United States
                                for consultation with the War Department.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>